        <headline>Beach Hazards Statement issued July 16 at 3:34PM EDT until July 18 at 2:00AM EDT by NWS Northern Indiana</headline>
        <description>* WHAT...High wave action, strong currents, and dangerous swimming
conditions expected. Piers will be heavily swamped by waves.
Waves 4 to 6 feet.

* WHERE...In Indiana, Northern La Porte county. In Michigan,
Berrien county.

* WHEN...From late tonight through late Thursday night.

* IMPACTS...Strong currents can pull swimmers into deeper water
and high waves can sweep people off piers.
</description>
        <instruction>Remain out of the water to avoid hazardous swimming conditions.
Do not venture out on piers.</instruction>
